{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '**1. Genesis AI Emerges from Stealth with $105M Funding for Universal Robotics Platform**  \n- **Date:** 2026-03-30  \n- **Details:** Genesis AI has officially emerged from stealth mode, securing $105 million in funding. The company aims to build a "universal robotics foundation model" and horizontal platform capable of generalizing across varied form factors and environments, indicating a major whale movement toward hardware-agnostic embodied intelligence. The round is backed by heavyweights including Khosla Ventures, Eclipse, Eric Schmidt, and Xavier Niel.  \n- **Source:** https://pulse2.com/genesis-ai-105-million-funding-details/  \n\n**2. Kuka Group Launches Kuka AMP in Partnership with Nvidia**  \n- **Date:** 2026-03-31  \n- **Details:** Global robotics manufacturer Kuka unveiled its "Kuka AMP" software platform at Nvidia GTC, signaling a major transition to "Automation 2.0." Concurrently, Nvidia launched its "Physical AI Data Factory Blueprint," directly complementing Kuka\'s ecosystem. This signals deep hardware-software integration between legacy robotics giants and dominant AI chip makers.  \n- **Source:** https://roboticsandautomationnews.com/2026/03/31/kuka-group-makes-its-move-into-automation-2-0-with-kuka-amp-platform/103239/  \n\n**3. LG Innotek & Applied Intuition Form Strategic Partnership for Drones and Robotics**  \n- **Date:** 2026-03-30  \n- **Details:** LG Innotek signed a strategic partnership with Silicon Valley-based Applied Intuition. The collaboration focuses on expanding LG\'s autonomous driving sensing and software expertise into broader embodied applications—specifically drones and robotics—to solidify leadership in the emerging physical AI market.  \n- **Source:** https://www.wowtv.co.kr/NewsCenter/News/Read?articleId=A202603300185 (Korean release)  \n\n**4. Rohto Pharmaceutical Launches Humanoid Co-Worker Manufacturing Project**  \n- **Date:** 2026-03-31  \n- **Details:** Japan\'s Rohto Pharmaceutical launched a dedicated "Humanoid Development Project" utilizing physical AI at its Ueno Techno Center. The goal is to quickly deploy humanoids alongside human workers on the manufacturing floor to alleviate chronic labor shortages.  \n- **Source:** https://news.yahoo.co.jp/articles/6dcdd8eb479cda81f1ec423c96f920f66b5c3ff9 (Japanese release)\n\n**5. Global X Australia Launches Dedicated Humanoid Robotics ETF (Ticker: HMND)**  \n- **Date:** 2026-03-31  \n- **Details:** Reflecting increasing institutional interest and capitalization of the sector, Global X launched the "Humanoid Robotics ETF" (ASX: HMND) in Australia. It aims to track the Solactive Global Humanoid Robotics Index, capturing value across the AI components, actuators, sensors, and materials supporting humanoid builds.  \n- **Source:** https://www.morningstar.com.au/news/pr-newswire/20260331ph67438/global-x-launches-humanoid-robotics-etf  \n\n**6. NGen Allocates $79.5M for Canadian AI Manufacturing, Boosting InDro Robotics**  \n- **Date:** 2026-03-31  \n- **Details:** Next Generation Manufacturing Canada (NGen) announced a $79.5 million CAD investment across 20 commercial AI projects. A notable beneficiary in the embodied space is InDro Robotics, which will use the funding to accelerate commercialization and global scaling of its physical AI integrations.  \n- **Source:** https://www.automationmag.com/ngen-announces-79-5-million-in-ai-funding/', 'thought_signature': 'CkcBjz1rX6CvlbKufTOnfFkAf-0eRX8LUwIHXYpIRXUC1rz5iWBy_HEAypbouDYaI2cTiAh-kdDnad4c2llC9zBoBGZbuU46oA=='}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {'grounding_supports': [{'grounding_chunk_indices': [0], 'segment': {'start_index': 460, 'end_index': 561, 'text': 'The round is backed by heavyweights including Khosla Ventures, Eclipse, Eric Schmidt, and Xavier Niel'}}, {'grounding_chunk_indices': [1, 2], 'segment': {'start_index': 1000, 'end_index': 1106, 'text': 'This signals deep hardware-software integrati