{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '### Daily Market Sweep Report: Physical AI and Embodied Robotics\n\n**Sector Sentiment:** **Very Bullish**\n\n#### **Market Dynamics & Key Takeaways**\n*   **Direct Impact:** Legacy hardware providers and leading AI software ecosystems are aggressively converging. Kuka’s launch of the AMP platform at Nvidia GTC, tightly coupled with Nvidia’s "Physical AI Data Factory Blueprint," reflects a systemic shift towards "Automation 2.0" where hardware becomes an actuation layer for universal software brains. Heavyweight backing for Genesis AI ($105M) validates the viability of hardware-agnostic, universal foundation models.\n*   **Indirect Impact:** Companies with legacy expertise in mobility sensors and specialty manufacturing are pivoting hard to generalized embodied AI. LG Innotek is applying autonomous vehicle sensing to drone and robotics pipelines via Applied Intuition, and Rohto Pharmaceutical is bypassing traditional automation solutions in favor of humanoid co-workers to combat labor shortages.\n*   **Macro/Capital Flows:** State and institutional capital flows indicate the sector is moving from pure R&D into immediate commercialization. The introduction of the Global X Humanoid Robotics ETF (ASX: HMND) creates a targeted investment vehicle for institutions, while NGen\'s $79.5M CAD injection gives substantial runway for sovereign manufacturing players like InDro Robotics.\n\n#### **Filtered Scout Findings (Post-Dedup)**\n\n| Date | Finding summary |\n| :--- | :--- |\n| **2026-03-30** | **Genesis AI Emerges from Stealth with $105M Funding:** Secured backing from Khosla Ventures, Eclipse, Eric Schmidt, and Xavier Niel to build a universal robotics foundation model and horizontal platform for various form factors. |\n| **2026-03-31** | **Kuka Group Launches Kuka AMP with Nvidia:** Kuka launched its "Automation 2.0" software platform at Nvidia GTC, heavily aligning with Nvidia\'s new Physical AI Data Factory Blueprint. |\n| **2026-03-30** | **LG Innotek & Applied Intuition Strategic Partnership:** LG Innotek will leverage its autonomous driving and sensor expertise for broader embodied applications (drones/robotics) in partnership with Applied Intuition. |\n| **2026-03-31** | **Rohto Pharmaceutical Humanoid Manufacturing Project:** Launched a Humanoid Development Project at its Ueno Techno Center to deploy humanoid co-workers and alleviate chronic labor shortages. |\n| **2026-03-31** | **Global X Australia HMND ETF Launch:** Global X launched a dedicated Humanoid Robotics ETF (ASX: HMND) tracking the Solactive Global Humanoid Robotics Index. |\n| **2026-03-31** | **NGen Allocates $79.5M for Canadian AI Manufacturing:** Next Generation Manufacturing Canada\'s major commercial AI fund includes heavy backing for InDro Robotics to accelerate its physical AI deployments. |\n\n*(Note: Data engineering and deduplication pipelines completed successfully. 6 unique findings verified. 4 ticker/market searches performed.)*', 'thought_signature': 'Cr8BAY89a1-CcmL2ZxD5kY4fIhczaH-cUClYPsU0_dxOofBYlEMzM6njviXtui0CBV5xgZIIh3oCDCRa_JTixnKVsfaInAlw3hHWNORJ8i_ykl8L3cLH0jfhkmsINycFtZFigyTTMdskGNfqLaOzahLyK1AvCOjAk2Hwt4vFiK1YS6i-SpEVJT5BRvq4d1kDW8RVnaNEkIW7hhWYQd1MSHkPjTliGxBXU4wWy5cE2pdBlqVgyk1d-XVHRFYe73syQog='}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 659, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 659}], 'prompt_token_count': 3069, 'prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 3069}], 'thoughts_token_count': 32, 'total_token_count': 3760, 'traffic_type': 'ON_DEMAND'}, 'invocation_id': 'e-4084cbbb-754a-4538-bdfa-8719ffac4441', 'author': 'Robotics_Scout_DE', 'actions': {'state_delta': {'Robotics_Scout_analyzed': '### Daily Market Sweep Report: Physical AI and Embodied Robotics\n\n**Sector Sentiment:** **Very Bullish**\n\n#### **Market Dynamics & Key Takeaways**\