{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '**Space Exploration and Defense Technology - Daily Market Sweep**\n**Date:** March 31, 2026\n\n### 1. Rocket Lab (RKLB) Secures Largest-Ever Launch Contract\n* **Catalyst:** Secured a historic $190M HASTE launch contract for U.S. DoD and allied hypersonic flight testing, pushing total backlog to >70 launches.\n* **Direct Takeaway:** Major structural pivot validated; RKLB is now a tier-1 prime contractor in the defense supply chain, moving beyond just commercial small-sat delivery.\n* **Indirect Takeaway:** Hypersonic testing demand is accelerating rapidly. The DoD is leveraging commercial launch providers to rapidly iterate testing at a lower cost curve.\n* **Market Dynamics & Technicals:** RKLB is trading near $64, boasting a market cap of ~$36.4B. It has seen monumental momentum over the last year.\n* **Sentiment:** **Very Bullish**\n\n### 2. Genenta Science (GNTA) Executes Aerospace M&A Binding Offer\n* **Catalyst:** Signed a binding offer to acquire up to 51% of Italian aerospace/defense manufacturer Sòphia High Tech, rebranding the entity as "Saentra Forge".\n* **Direct Takeaway:** Drastic operational pivot for GNTA (traditionally a biotech) into AI-enhanced European aerospace manufacturing and localized defense production. \n* **Indirect Takeaway:** European defense localization and onshoring is driving aggressive M&A, forcing micro-caps to pivot completely to capture available defense capital.\n* **Market Dynamics & Technicals:** The market is deeply skeptical. The stock is heavily depressed, trading at $0.63 (down ~84% over the last year) with a micro-cap valuation of just $16.6M.\n* **Sentiment:** **Bearish** (Technicals/Price Action) / **Neutral** (Strategic Pivot)\n\n### 3. Astroscale & Isar Aerospace Formalize ELSA-M Launch Contract\n* **Catalyst:** Astroscale (TODA Corp subsidiary) executed a binding FY 2028 commercial launch contract with Isar Aerospace for the ELSA-M mission (multi-client End-of-Life debris removal).\n* **Direct Takeaway:** Secures the launch vehicle (Spectrum) for the first definitive commercial debris removal mission, validating the execution timeline for ELSA-M.\n* **Indirect Takeaway:** Strong signal for the European commercial space ecosystem; Isar Aerospace is successfully winning high-profile institutional and commercial EOL payloads against legacy providers.\n* **Market Dynamics & Technicals:** Commercial validation of the "space sustainability" sub-sector; regulatory pressures are likely creating a definitive revenue model for EOL services. \n* **Sentiment:** **Bullish**', 'thought_signature': 'Cl4Bjz1rXwzciHinTfbrnGXWxgi5otxeCKeQWYG0zbOugonaEdSTIzb6FXqcJWJflIMcecjxTpGTd_PecYfeRG2s-hFV95nYpAD6FyOD0KsRq4TrJyz8DLoDErhQVW7xCr4CAY89a188xyQpVTs0ZmUJEWlBFQ2jes5D5nPfXs6wh4NnDUdyl8av1pHpCuOfNB-7fi1taLRKVdthCtjhVJMw921O9dk7uZgW4V0Y9mmc83mGiMT_rFA3fS_U8jih3qY1CLgFhIF3JIOfSzOTfNKCjsgurHxtNRtSxFAxAB0kJ6gIkvnZdAFElyRYP3cQ9JmshJ1yZE5PMCYLd2SemD7DftOtcdBROPLR9P0PPvcct9s7s7Z_2CNGXjir6Zfy7bZO-NqRxopSY1gGXfmMJcxx_3st-b60ptoFWrcQDZSfE9ChIPP4UJi05b1RcUFzInwUyZn0UagA7ywuj8xKKYpaajCPc4_6-j__outK7E037XThh6UmWIAI2KvwBcVtPE9luPo_I5q2jKoszkb89spAJQM4KK8hVaFYq2mzn8kI'}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {'grounding_chunks': [{'web': {'domain': 'hexn.io', 'title': 'hexn.io', 'uri': 'https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQGdQ-QMn0Qfg94PINpoAH8IbIdc5Fl7PEPHKRUADo7K8GjGlFOSEzOuc5ojw8QX_xkxirQy8u7wk2S6nq905WHI8VAUTAwxxOompSvtVPAg-lWdcbi_y5BiPO-15sNC82_LiDvjxFo='}}, {'web': {'domain': 'benzinga.com', 'title': 'benzinga.com', 'uri': 'https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQFPDGxkOm1ja5gDJgtEKdmCOoMqppT-FzuxaaXaT9PR-yXns9rCBY2KtMzyiFUpdAy1uyJD9DaHJvOUPsZev7V73gnLoEUsDXZ9uKBlfIG5L3egnIVgpBE-R1NvbFM='}}, {'web': {'domain': 'stocktitan.net', 'title': 'stocktitan.net', 'uri': 'https://vertexaisearch.cloud.google.com/grounding-api-redirect/AUZIYQEDKhbi4BQIpsGgQbYxO-8Xk5C0cmrdKlq7nuSCsJv