ecutes Aerospace M&A Binding Offer\n* **Catalyst:** Signed a binding offer to acquire up to 51% of Italian aerospace/defense manufacturer Sòphia High Tech, rebranding the entity as "Saentra Forge".\n* **Direct Takeaway:** Drastic operational pivot for GNTA (traditionally a biotech) into AI-enhanced European aerospace manufacturing and localized defense production. \n* **Indirect Takeaway:** European defense localization and onshoring is driving aggressive M&A, forcing micro-caps to pivot completely to capture available defense capital.\n* **Market Dynamics & Technicals:** The market is deeply skeptical. The stock is heavily depressed, trading at $0.63 (down ~84% over the last year) with a micro-cap valuation of just $16.6M.\n* **Sentiment:** **Bearish** (Technicals/Price Action) / **Neutral** (Strategic Pivot)\n\n### 3. Astroscale & Isar Aerospace Formalize ELSA-M Launch Contract\n* **Catalyst:** Astroscale (TODA Corp subsidiary) executed a binding FY 2028 commercial launch contract with Isar Aerospace for the ELSA-M mission (multi-client End-of-Life debris removal).\n* **Direct Takeaway:** Secures the launch vehicle (Spectrum) for the first definitive commercial debris removal mission, validating the execution timeline for ELSA-M.\n* **Indirect Takeaway:** Strong signal for the European commercial space ecosystem; Isar Aerospace is successfully winning high-profile institutional and commercial EOL payloads against legacy providers.\n* **Market Dynamics & Technicals:** Commercial validation of the "space sustainability" sub-sector; regulatory pressures are likely creating a definitive revenue model for EOL services. \n* **Sentiment:** **Bullish**'}, 'artifact_delta': {}, 'requested_auth_configs': {}, 'requested_tool_confirmations': {}}, 'branch': 'Batch_2.Space_Defense_Scout_Pipeline', 'id': 'f54a77ea-b6ec-480c-accb-23fb62096789', 'timestamp': 1774996482.1756072}Tools at indices [0] are not compatible with automatic function calling (AFC). AFC is disabled. If AFC is