{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '1. **Hastings Technology Metals Acquires Thai Hydrometallurgical REE Facility** (2026-03-31)\nHastings Technology Metals, in a strategic partnership with Wyloo, has acquired a fully-permitted hydrometallurgical mixed rare earth chloride (MREC) production facility in Thailand, positioning itself to disrupt existing critical mineral supply chains heavily controlled by China. \n*Source: https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/31/3052822/0/en/Ucore-Congratulates-Hastings-on-its-Acquisition-and-New-Strategic-Direction-with-Wyloo.html*\n\n2. **Mitsubishi Materials Corporation Invests in ReElement Technologies** (2026-03-31)\nMitsubishi Materials Corporation announced a strategic investment into Indiana-based ReElement Technologies Corporation. The investment focuses on advancing rare earth and rare metal recycling technologies in the United States.\n*Source: https://finance.yahoo.com/news/mitsubishi-materials-corporation-announces-decision-120000407.html*\n\n3. **Lloyds Metals and Energy Ltd (LMEL) Acquires CHEMAF Group** (2026-03-31)\nIndian steelmaker Lloyds Metals and Energy Ltd has formally announced its intent to acquire the DRC-based CHEMAF Group, a major player in copper and cobalt mining. This acquisition directly targets the critical EV battery metals supply chain. \n*Source: https://www.steelguru.com/steel/lloyds-metals-to-acquire-congo-s-chemaf-for-securing-battery-metals/56195*\n\n4. **European Lithium Expands into Titanium via Velta Holding Acquisition** (2026-03-31)\nEuropean Lithium is expanding its strategic mineral portfolio into titanium and other critical minerals by acquiring UAH 8.95 billion in claims against Ukraine\'s Velta Holding, moving to integrate Velta into its corporate structure.\n*Source: https://asterslaw.com/news/asters_advises_european_lithium_on_claim_acquisition_against_velta_holding_to_further_integrate_it_into_its_structure/*\n\n5. **Cobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals Consortium for Project Infinity** (2026-03-30)\nCobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals have launched a consortium to co-develop "Project Infinity." The project aims to establish a polymetallic nodule processing facility in the US Gulf Coast, with an expected annual throughput of approximately 200,000 tonnes of critical ocean-derived minerals.\n*Source: https://finance.yahoo.com/news/cobalt-blue-asx-cob-glomar-050000287.html*\n\n6. **Lithium Africa Corp. Acquires 30% of Springbok Lithium Project** (2026-03-30)\nLithium Africa Corp (LAC) has signed an agreement to acquire a 30% interest in Namli Exploration & Mining\'s Springbok Project, marking a significant early-stage consolidation in South African lithium deposits.\n*Source: https://stockhouse.com/news/press-releases/2026/03/30/lithium-africa-corp-announces-acquisition-of-30-interest-in-namli-exploration*\n\n7. **USA Rare Earth Secures Controversial $1.6B US Government Funding** (2026-03-30)\nUSA Rare Earth has been slated to receive up to $1.6 billion in government backing for the Round Top heavy rare earth and lithium deposit in Texas. The funding has sparked controversy due to financial ties between the company and US Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick’s family firm, Cantor Fitzgerald.\n*Source: https://nypost.com/2026/03/30/business/howard-lutnicks-cantor-fitzgerald-firm-to-get-payout-from-grant/*\n\n8. **Tsodilo Resources Integrates AI for Rare Earth Targeting in Botswana** (2026-03-30)\nTsodilo Resources announced a new partnership with Battelle Memorial Institute to integrate AI into its exploration models for the Gcwihaba rare earth project, representing a high-tech pivot for early-stage African strategic mineral exploration.\n*Source: https://news.mongabay.com/2026/03/botswanas-mining-firms-turn-to-ai-for-discovery-despite-environmental-risks/*', 'thought_signature': 'CkEBjz1rX4jhBguH8iptbooLNY0uF-BcbWGfAkHJ8bS0aQuzWnOgoJI5xtw4OgaU-qHksNiuEJjlKkWZryDMrOyDbA=='}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 1032, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 1032}], 'prompt_token_count': 377, 'prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 377}], 'thoughts_token_count': 8, 'tool_use_prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT'}], 'total_token_count': 1417, 'traffic_type': 'ON_DEMAND'}, 'invocation_id': 'e-860c9d30-7755-4ac4-8875-ca5a1df36b26', 'author': 'Strategic_Minerals_Scout', 'actions': {'state_delta': {'Strategic_Minerals_Scout_findings': '1. **Hastings Technology Metals Acquires Thai Hydrometallurgical REE Facility** (2026-03-31)\nHastings Technology Metals, in a strategic partnership with Wyloo, has acquired a fully-permitted hydrometallurgical mixed rare earth chloride (MREC) production facility in Thailand, positioning itself to disrupt existing critical mineral supply chains heavily controlled by China. \n*Source: https://www.globenewswire.com/news-release/2026/03/31/3052822/0/en/Ucore-Congratulates-Hastings-on-its-Acquisition-and-New-Strategic-Direction-with-Wyloo.html*\n\n2. **Mitsubishi Materials Corporation Invests in ReElement Technologies** (2026-03-31)\nMitsubishi Materials Corporation announced a strategic investment into Indiana-based ReElement Technologies Corporation. The investment focuses on advancing rare earth and rare metal recycling technologies in the United States.\n*Source: https://finance.yahoo.com/news/mitsubishi-materials-corporation-announces-decision-120000407.html*\n\n3. **Lloyds Metals and Energy Ltd (LMEL) Acquires CHEMAF Group** (2026-03-31)\nIndian steelmaker Lloyds Metals and Energy Ltd has formally announced its intent to acquire the DRC-based CHEMAF Group, a major player in copper and cobalt mining. This acquisition directly targets the critical EV battery metals supply chain. \n*Source: https://www.steelguru.com/steel/lloyds-metals-to-acquire-congo-s-chemaf-for-securing-battery-metals/56195*\n\n4. **European Lithium Expands into Titanium via Velta Holding Acquisition** (2026-03-31)\nEuropean Lithium is expanding its strategic mineral portfolio into titanium and other critical minerals by acquiring UAH 8.95 billion in claims against Ukraine\'s Velta Holding, moving to integrate Velta into its corporate structure.\n*Source: https://asterslaw.com/news/asters_advises_european_lithium_on_claim_acquisition_against_velta_holding_to_further_integrate_it_into_its_structure/*\n\n5. **Cobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals Consortium for Project Infinity** (2026-03-30)\nCobalt Blue and Glomar Minerals have launched a consortium to co-develop "Project Infinity." The project aims to establish a polymetallic nodule processing facility in the US Gulf Coast, with an expected annual throughput of approximately 200,000 tonnes of critical ocean-derived minerals.\n*Source: https://finance.yahoo.com/news/cobalt-blue-asx-cob-glomar-050000287.html*\n\n6. **Lithium Africa Corp. Acquires 30% of Springbok Lithium Project** (2026-03-30)\nLithium Africa Corp (LAC) has signed an agreement to acquire a 30% interest in Namli Exploration & Mining\'s Springbok Project, marking a significant early-stage consolidation in South African lithium deposits.\n*Source: https://stockhouse.com/news/press-releases/2026/03/30/lithium-africa-corp-announces-acquisition-of-30-interest-in-namli-exploration*\n\n7. **USA Rare Earth Secures Controversial $1.6B US Government Funding** (2026-03-30)\nUSA Rare Earth has been slated to receive up to $1.6 billion in government backing for the Round Top heavy rare earth and lithium deposit in Texas. The funding has sparked controversy due to financial ties between the company and US Commerce Secretary Howard Lutnick’s family firm, Cantor Fitzgerald.\n*Source: https://nypost.com/2026/03/30/business/howard-lutnicks-cantor-fitzgerald-firm-to-get-payout-from-grant/*\n\n8. **Tsodilo Resources Integrates AI for Rare Earth Targeting in Botswana** (2026-03-30)\nTsodilo Resources announced a new 