{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '1. **EnerVenue Secures $300M Series B Extension for Grid-Scale ESS**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-31\n   - **Details**: Hong Kong property tycoon Peter Lee (via Full Vision Capital) led a $300M Series B extension in California-based energy storage startup EnerVenue. The funding aims to scale up the industrial application of its nickel-hydrogen batteries—especially to meet surging demand from AI data centers—and will establish a regional HQ and R&D center in Hong Kong.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.forbes.com/\n\n2. **Canadian Solar’s e-STORAGE Inks 420 MWh BESS Deal with Drax Group**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-31\n   - **Details**: e-STORAGE has secured a contract to deliver a 420 MWh fully integrated battery energy storage system (using its SolBank 3.0 technology) across two projects for Drax Group in the UK. The rollout includes a 60 MW/120 MWh system in Marfleet and a 150 MW/300 MWh system in Neilston.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.prnewswire.com/\n\n3. **Flex Acquires Electrical Power Products (EP²) for $1.1 Billion**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Details**: Flex announced a definitive agreement to acquire EP², a provider of engineered-to-order electrical power control and protection systems, in an all-cash transaction valued at $1.1 billion. This major M&A move positions Flex to capitalize heavily on grid modernization, energy electrification, and power management for AI data centers.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.prnewswire.com/\n\n4. **MTerra Solar Energizes Tranche of World’s Largest Battery-Integrated Solar Project**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Details**: Meralco PowerGen Corp. (MGEN) began exporting an initial 250 MW to the grid from its MTerra Solar project in the Philippines. As part of this launch, it successfully energized the first tranche of its colossal 4,500-MWh battery energy storage system, which will allow consistent daytime renewable energy to be delivered reliably at night.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.bworldonline.com/\n\n5. **Qnetic Kicks Off Flywheel ESS Manufacturing & New Funding Push**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Details**: Kinetic/Flywheel energy storage startup Qnetic is retrofitting a California factory to begin low-volume manufacturing of its Q500 solid-state mechanical battery systems for grid services. The company concurrently launched a $5M RegCF campaign as part of a $20M funding sprint projected for 2026.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.energy-storage.news/', 'thought_signature': 'Cq0CAY89a19lOdgTlclTzEwccJZEHDxNXr8XhCipOmm8t9uYBsN8JPXyX5yjSpAjbqBR5ZTdlVhARbcWSpQNSu2mxoaYE7BNdcQpYZ9cYLLlREMiM483_VZQRGJklRHhB01Q9EOatVks209YSLhwWoPvL-04N-WYiUK86UtPUv_GXj6JLyZHXNq449kG70Y1t0Jo_f9KCpuUYFo_CwIOwGP96rzsdZWaoGkDBByKyB3MxDwZ21XR-9NfyxwK6IM1EMVRu6DCl9yKBATSoyp5UVRJAhWPYucoC5Yn4Ytswz2JzfqVOFWZHuRaAyb6VASUtBDKzedqC88lnFOWIdvtn3Bhm3OsUZeuv3FUtj-nJn6NzQYjub7Y-OJGlZCm8lD0FIhA8AaMVTdUar2JCBNmbQ=='}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 667, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 667}], 'prompt_token_count': 370, 'prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 370}], 'thoughts_token_count': 55, 'tool_use_prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT'}], 'total_token_count': 1092, 'traffic_type': 'ON_DEMAND'}, 'invocation_id': 'e-860c9d30-7755-4ac4-8875-ca5a1df36b26', 'author': 'Power_Energy_Scout', 'actions': {'state_delta': {'Power_Energy_Scout_findings': '1. **EnerVenue Secures $300M Series B Extension for Grid-Scale ESS**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-31\n   - **Details**: Hong Kong property tycoon Peter Lee (via Full Vision Capital) led a $300M Series B extension in California-based energy storage startup EnerVenue. The funding aims to scale up the industrial application of its nickel-hydrogen batteries—especially to meet surging demand from AI data centers—and will establish a regional HQ and R&D center in Hong Kong.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.forbes.com/\n\n2. **Canadian Solar’s e-STORAGE Inks 420 MWh BESS Deal with Drax Group**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-31\n   - **Details**: e-STORAGE has secured a contract to deliver a 420 MWh fully integrated battery energy storage system (using its SolBank 3.0 technology) across two projects for Drax Group in the UK. The rollout includes a 60 MW/120 MWh system in Marfleet and a 150 MW/300 MWh system in Neilston.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.prnewswire.com/\n\n3. **Flex Acquires Electrical Power Products (EP²) for $1.1 Billion**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Details**: Flex announced a definitive agreement to acquire EP², a provider of engineered-to-order electrical power control and protection systems, in an all-cash transaction valued at $1.1 billion. This major M&A move positions Flex to capitalize heavily on grid modernization, energy electrification, and power management for AI data centers.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.prnewswire.com/\n\n4. **MTerra Solar Energizes Tranche of World’s Largest Battery-Integrated Solar Project**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Details**: Meralco PowerGen Corp. (MGEN) began exporting an initial 250 MW to the grid from its MTerra Solar project in the Philippines. As part of this launch, it successfully energized the first tranche of its colossal 4,500-MWh battery energy storage system, which will allow consistent daytime renewable energy to be delivered reliably at night.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.bworldonline.com/\n\n5. **Qnetic Kicks Off Flywheel ESS Manufacturing & New Funding Push**\n   - **Published Date**: 2026-03-30\n   - **Details**: Kinetic/Flywheel energy storage startup Qnetic is retrofitting a California factory to begin low-volume manufacturing of its Q500 solid-state mechanical battery systems for grid services. The company concurrently launched a $5M RegCF campaign as part of a $20M funding sprint projected for 2026.\n   - **Source URL**: https://www.energy-storage.news/'}, 'artifact_delta': {}, 'requested_auth_configs': {}, 'requested_tool_confirmations': {}}, 'branch': 'Batch_3.Power_Energy_Scout_Pipeline', 'id': '62767b48-60f3-4737-8e45-dc4b3ff24abc', 'timestamp': 1774996714.5972986}
