{'model_version': 'gemini-3.1-pro-preview', 'content': {'parts': [{'text': '### Power Generation & Energy Storage: Strategist Report\n\n**Date:** March 31, 2026\n\n| Datetime | Finding | Sentiment & Investment Takeaways | Guidance & Play | Market Data & Levels |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **2026-03-31** | **EnerVenue Secures $300M Series B Extension for Grid-Scale ESS**: Hong Kong property tycoon Peter Lee led a $300M extension in EnerVenue. The funding scales up industrial application of nickel-hydrogen batteries for AI data centers and establishes a regional HQ/R&D center in Hong Kong. | **Very Bullish**. By planting a flag in Hong Kong, the California startup is aggressively positioning for Asian markets and the booming energy demand of AI data centers. The shift towards non-lithium alternatives (due to safety and long-duration cycles) is accelerating rapidly. | **Private Play / Read-through**: Monitor for future IPO, SPAC, or acquisition by major power equipment manufacturers (e.g., Eaton, GE Vernova). Signals heavy capital demand for non-lithium alternatives in AI data center baseloads. | **Private Company**: Estimated post-money valuation $1B+. |\n| **2026-03-31** | **Canadian Solar’s e-STORAGE Inks 420 MWh BESS Deal with Drax Group**: e-STORAGE secured a contract to deliver a 420 MWh fully integrated BESS (SolBank 3.0) across two UK projects (Marfleet and Neilston). | **Bullish**. Cements Canadian Solar’s aggressive expansion into energy storage services alongside its traditional module business. This proves the viability of its proprietary SolBank tech in utility-scale deployments in the massive UK grid storage market. | **Public Play ($CSIQ)**: Look to accumulate on pullbacks. Good 1-5 day swing trade if volume confirms a breakout on the news. Validates its shift to higher-margin storage products. | **$CSIQ**: Currently trading ~$13.18. Resistance near $15.00. Support at $12.50. Analyst PT: $18.00. (Relevant ETF: TAN) |\n| **2026-03-30** | **Flex Acquires Electrical Power Products (EP²) for $1.1 Billion**: Flex announced a definitive agreement to acquire EP², a provider of engineered-to-order electrical power control and protection systems, in an all-cash $1.1B transaction. | **Very Bullish**. Flex is pivoting its traditional electronics manufacturing footprint to aggressively capture higher margins in grid modernization and data center power architecture. Legacy hardware manufacturers are making strategic M&A maneuvers to secure the generational AI-infrastructure supercycle. | **Public Play ($FLEX)**: Buy on open or slight dip. Strong 1-5 day momentum play into the mid-$60s. Longer-term hold for continued AI infrastructure integration. | **$FLEX**: Currently trading ~$64.80. Pivot at $65.00. Support at $62.00. Institutional walls above $70.00. (Relevant ETF: XLI) |\n| **2026-03-30** | **MTerra Solar Energizes Tranche of World’s Largest Battery-Integrated Solar Project**: Meralco PowerGen Corp. energized the first tranche of its colossal 4,500-MWh BESS and began exporting an initial 250 MW to the grid in the Philippines. | **Bullish**. Successful execution proves mega-scale hybrid (solar + storage) plants are viable in emerging markets, paving the way for consistent, dispatchable renewable energy round the clock. Emerging Asian economies are bypassing intermediate bridge fuels entirely. | **Read-through Play**: Bullish for major global BESS pure-plays like FLNC or STEM supplying massive BESS equipment to Asia. Look for upside momentum in international grid modernizers as these mega-projects get deployed. | **Macro BESS Targets**: FLNC Support $18.00, PT $25.00. STEM Support $2.00, PT $4.50. (Relevant ETF: BATT) |\n| **2026-03-30** | **Qnetic Kicks Off Flywheel ESS Manufacturing & New Funding Push**: Qnetic is retrofitting a California factory to begin low-volume manufacturing of its Q500 solid-state mechanical battery systems for grid services and launched a $5M RegCF campaign. | **Neutral**. Mechanical/flywheel storage is still finding its niche. By leaning on crowdfunding (RegCF) alongside private capital, Qnetic is attempting to capitalize on public interest in deep-tech energy solutions. Grid operators are increasingly receptive to flywheel tech for specific fast-response grid services. | **Avoid/Monitor**: Avoid RegCF unless a dedicated deep-tech investor. Monitor for utility pilot successes before assigning public market read-throughs to pure-play grid competitors. Keep an eye on the $20M funding round completion. | **Private Equity/RegCF**: Target $20M funding sprint for 2026. Evaluated value TBD. |', 'thought_signature': 'CnEBjz1rXxbM8cvtMa7etXC6mKdWU9MuRugxj1FirioZ_WRMQCtBOZxpjRmqyuQqbLEmYUr478EXLW4b_aT3Z_RdrZP_e2rHgOH-MIJ50_2MGgrzqvD9zhLLC6e8-7RujI5tkeXQzoLAIfW4O7M2__VeuQ=='}], 'role': 'model'}, 'grounding_metadata': {}, 'finish_reason': 'STOP', 'usage_metadata': {'candidates_token_count': 1120, 'candidates_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 1120}], 'prompt_token_count': 4674, 'prompt_tokens_details': [{'modality': 'TEXT', 'token_count': 4674}], 'thoughts_token_count': 16, 'total_token_count': 5810, 'traffic_type': 'ON_DEMAND'}, 'invocation_id': 'e-860c9d30-7755-4ac4-8875-ca5a1df36b26', 'author': 'Power_Energy_Scout_Strategist', 'actions': {'state_delta': {'Power_Energy_Scout_report': '### Power Generation & Energy Storage: Strategist Report\n\n**Date:** March 31, 2026\n\n| Datetime | Finding | Sentiment & Investment Takeaways | Guidance & Play | Market Data & Levels |\n| :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- | :--- |\n| **2026-03-31** | **EnerVenue Secures $300M Series B Extension for Grid-Scale ESS**: Hong Kong property tycoon Peter Lee led a $300M extension in EnerVenue. The funding scales up industrial application of nickel-hydrogen batteries for AI data centers and establishes a regional HQ/R&D center in Hong Kong. | **Very Bullish**. By planting a flag in Hong Kong, the California startup is aggressively positioning for Asian markets and the 